<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-20T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-20T06:00:00-05:00" n="1354" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1354">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/7–2045: Telegram</note>
                            <head>No. 1354<lb/><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United
                                    Kingdom</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJG2" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-20T12:00:00+01:00">July 20,
                                    1945—noon</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>7304. Embassy understands Foreign Office position unchanged by French
                                proposals (re Paris 525, July 18 to London<note n="1" xml:id="d1354fn1"><ref target="#d1350">Document No.
                                    1350</ref>.</note>) British still unwilling proceed prior
                                conclusion Big Three Meeting. Should meeting end in time, and result
                                in concurrence Soviet request as is expected, British will make
                                counter-proposal Tangier Conference to open August 6 instead August
                                3.</p>
                            <p>Sent <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> as 7304; repeated Paris
                                467, Madrid 192, Tangier 45.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_WJG2"><hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>